386→                        <div id="content">For a triangle-free graph $G$ let $h_r(G)$ be the smallest number of edges that need to be added to $G$ so that it has diameter $r$ (while preserving the property of being triangle-free).<br><br>Is it true that there exists a constant $c&#62;0$ such that if $G$ is a connected graph on $n$ vertices then $h_4(G)&#60;(1-c)n$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/619">#619</a>: <a href="#cite-EGR98-619" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('EGR98','619'); return false;">[EGR98]</a><a href="#cite-Er99-619" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er99','619'); return false;">[Er99]</a></div>
