408→                           A problem of Erdős, Gyárfás, and Ruszinkó <a href="#cite-EGR98-619" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('EGR98','619'); return false;">[EGR98]</a> who proved that $h_3(G)\leq n$ and $h_5(G) \leq \frac{n-1}{2}$ and there exist connected graphs $G$ on $n$ vertices with $h_3(G)\geq n-c$ for some constant $c&gt;0$.<br><br>If we omit the condition that the graph must remain triangle-free then Alon, Gyárfás, and Ruszinkó <a href="#cite-AGR00-619" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('AGR00','619'); return false;">[AGR00]</a> have proved that adding $n/2$ edges always suffices to obtain diameter at most $4$.<br><br>See also <a href="/134" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc" target="_blank">[134]</a> and <a href="/618" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer ugc" target="_blank">[618]</a>.
